<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-30T07:40:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-30T07:40:00-05:00" n="409" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d409">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 704.9339/2</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Russell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Santo Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-30T08:00:00-04:40">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 30, 1918, 8 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Referring to my cable of May 2, 4 p.m., in regard to Chinese, please
                            answer, as there are many Chinamen here who want to go to China by way
                            of New York and the steamers will not accept them without passports.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>